<DocsLayout title="buoy commands" description="Manage Claude Code slash commands">
  <h1>buoy commands</h1>

  <p>
    Install Buoy's slash commands to Claude Code. These commands give you quick access
    to design system workflows directly from Claude Code's command palette.
  </p>

  <h2>Usage</h2>

  <pre><code>buoy commands list              # List available commands
buoy commands install           # Install commands to ~/.claude/commands/</code></pre>

  <h2>Subcommands</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Subcommand</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>list</code></td>
        <td>List available Buoy slash commands and installation status</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>install</code></td>
        <td>Install commands to <code>~/.claude/commands/</code></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Options</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Option</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--dry-run</code></td>
        <td>Show what would be installed without writing files</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--json</code></td>
        <td>Output result as JSON</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Available Commands</h2>

  <h3>/contribution-loop</h3>

  <p>
    Autonomous workflow for finding repos with design drift and generating PRs to fix them.
    Runs through discovery, scanning, analysis, and PR generation phases.
  </p>

  <p>Phases:</p>

  <ol>
    <li><strong>Discovery</strong> — Find repos using design systems on GitHub</li>
    <li><strong>Scanning</strong> — Run Buoy to detect drift</li>
    <li><strong>Analysis</strong> — Use agents to assess fixability</li>
    <li><strong>Triage</strong> — Classify as slam-dunk, review, or skip</li>
    <li><strong>Generation</strong> — Create PR with full context</li>
    <li><strong>Review</strong> — Human approval before submission</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Example Output</h2>

  <pre><code>$ buoy commands list

  Available Buoy Commands

  /contribution-loop  not installed

  Run `buoy commands install` to install all commands

$ buoy commands install

  ✓ Installed slash commands:

    /contribution-loop

  Commands installed to: ~/.claude/commands/
  Restart Claude Code to use them</code></pre>

  <h2>Where Commands Are Installed</h2>

  <p>
    Commands are installed to <code>~/.claude/commands/</code>. This is Claude Code's
    global commands directory. After installation, restart Claude Code to see the new
    commands in the slash command palette.
  </p>

  <h2>Commands vs Skills</h2>

  <p>
    <strong>Commands</strong> are user-invocable — you type <code>/contribution-loop</code>
    in Claude Code to trigger them. <strong>Skills</strong> are AI-invocable — Claude
    automatically loads them when relevant.
  </p>

  <p>
    Use <code>buoy onboard</code> to create skills, and <code>buoy commands install</code>
    to install slash commands.
  </p>

